<item>
            <title>[LU-555] ll_have_md_lock() code optimization</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-555</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Suggested by Andreas:&lt;br/&gt;
in ll_md_blocking_ast(), Instead of doing multiple searches for these lock bits, it makes more sense to change ll_have_md_lock() to take &quot;&amp;amp;bits&quot; as the parameter (instead of a specific single bit), and then it can do a search on the first bit in the mask. If any lock is found, it can zero out all of the set lock bits in the lock from &quot;&amp;amp;bits&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the common case where there are multiple bits set in the lock this will avoid calling ll_have_md_lock-&amp;gt;md_lock_match() multiple times for each file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="11420">LU-555</key>
